content: Sketching again after being inspired by the art scene here. Sometimes, a change of scenery sparks creativity. #NYCInspires
Just turned 22 and reflecting on the journey so far. Tokyo was a dream, but NYC feels like coming home to my ambitions.
I've been diving into Solidity tutorials. It's like learning a new language, but with the potential to build something groundbreaking.
Pitched my trading model to a small fintech startup. They're interested in testing it with their data. Fingers crossed!
Mentorship session was intense today. Learned about resilience from failures. It's not just about coding or trading; it's about growth.
Back to the blockchain café. This time, I presented my identity verification idea. They're intrigued, and we're setting up a follow-up meeting.
Had an awkward encounter at a networking event. Tried to impress someone with my trading model, but they thought I was talking about video game trading cards. 😂
Progress on the trading model is steady. The mentor's insights are invaluable. If this works, it could be a game-changer.
Another step forward with Solidity. Built a simple contract that transfers tokens. It's basic, but it's mine, and it works!
The blockchain startup is looking for a developer with smart contract experience. Been grinding on Solidity for this moment. Time to shine.
Caught up with some old friends. It's grounding to have a support system, especially when you're pushing boundaries in tech.
Just got off a call with the fintech startup. They want to integrate my model into their platform for a trial run. This could be huge.
If life's a simulation, I'm coding my own narrative now. The blockchain project is shaping up, and my trading model is on the verge of real-world testing. Here's to the next chapter.
